			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=293952">Eastern Wastes</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>Coldain Insignia Ring quests (Spoiler Information)</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Coldain Insignia Ring quests (Spoiler Information)</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=324027"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:dargathi@mjphelan.f9.co.uk">Dargathi</a> | 
		                        1/4/2001 7:07:09 PM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Firstly all of this information is available here, but spread over several quests, all I have done is to compile it, and order it. I have not personally completed any part of this quest, I plan to start it tonight and see how far I can get, but having read all the posts here that seam to point to bits of it I decided to compile a post of as much as possible.<BR>
<BR>
This quest appears to have 8 segments to it<BR>
<BR>
First segment: Copper Coldain Insignia ring<BR>
------------------------------------------------<BR>
In one of the many Coldain camps holds a man named Garadain Glacierbane. If you hail him, and reply to him using the words in the brackets (like normal), he will ask you to sew him a blanket. The items you need to make the blanket are 2 snow panther and Kodiak pelts of the finest quality (I forget the name of the Kodiak, they are the bear/wolverine looking things in the wastes).<BR>
<BR>
The items needed are:<BR>
2 High Quality Tundra Kodiak Skins/Pelts<BR>
Found in Eastern Wastes from Tundra Kodiaks.<BR>
2 High Quality Cougar Skins<BR>
Found in Eastern Wastes and Iceclad from Snow Cougars.<BR>
<BR>
Notes:<BR>
<BR>
Trivial at 82 Tailoring<BR>
Snow cougars are easily soloed as a ranger at L39<BR>
Tundra Kodiaks are solo able as a ranger at L39<BR>
<BR>
A party of well-organized 25-35 can achieve great success here.<BR>
<BR>
Second segment: Silver Coldain Insignia ring<BR>
------------------------------------------------<BR>
Protect Boridain Glacierbane... he is at roughly -2500, 1500 location. Hand him the axe you get from Garadain. He will then go on a long journey to hunt down the Rabid Tundra. Eventually he makes it back to his spawn point, says a few words, and then the Rabid Tundra Kodiak will spawn. Kill him fast and don&#8217;t let boridain get killed. Loot the hide off the Kodiak and give boridain the skin. He will return a damaged axe (lore no drop) to return to Garadain. Give Garadain the copper ring and the damaged axe and receive the Silver Coldain Insignia ring.<BR>
<BR>
Notes:<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
To be safe, and to guarantee success here use two groups of 3 tank, chanter, druid/shaman<BR>
<BR>
One group follows Boridain and ensures he lives, the second group tracks the Rabid Tundra Kodiak and kills it, Rangers are especially good as the tank in this group.<BR>
<BR>
Third segment: Gold Coldain Insignia ring<BR>
------------------------------------------------<BR>
Garadain needs a new skinning knife. Get a sharpening stone (found on the ground in various locations across the zone), a high quality walrus skin, and a wooly rhino horn (yes horn, even though he asks for a tusk). Go to a forge and combine those three items. Was trivial at 190 skill. Return him the ring and the skinning knife for the Gold Coldain Insignia Ring<BR>
<BR>
Notes:<BR>
<BR>
Get smithing to 101 or more first.<BR>
<BR>
All of these mobs can be taken by a level 25-35 group. Fairly easily although the Rhino's gore is fairly nasty. The walrus and Rhinos all spawn in a pack around loc 0,0<BR>
<BR>
Fourth segment: Platinum Coldain Insignia Ring<BR>
------------------------------------------------<BR>
Garadain says the knife you just delivered is not high enough quality. He asks for a Coldain smithing hammer. Tells you that you can get one from Tain Frostbight. Deliver him the note to Tain. Tain is at roughly neg4800, neg2400 (don&#8217;t recall exact loc now) its straight out from bridge. Hail him and give note. Giving note doesn&#8217;t do much. He asks for help. Once you say you will help him, he says that he needs an item off of Khrak (named giant) and the giant and a group of giants spawn over the hill toward the bridge. They come rushing at him to kill him. Kill the named giant, get the item off him, and hand it in to Tain. Of course keep Tain alive during this fight (it was rather nasty fight for us band of 4). He will give you the coldain smithing hammer at that point. Go back to Garadain and give him the hammer and the ring. You get the platinum Coldain insignia ring. <BR>
<BR>
Notes:<BR>
<BR>
Once again I would advise 2 groups, this time however with a much higher-level enchanter, or necromancer, use mez and fear/snare kiting to dispatch the giants, and again 1 group defends Tain and the second takes out the giants.<BR>
<BR>
Assign someone to always have Tain in view, and perhaps even have a cleric dedicated to healing Tain.<BR>
<BR>
Fifth segment: Obsidian Coldain Insignia ring<BR>
------------------------------------------------<BR>
This quest starts with killing the Orc Messenger in East Wastes. He drops the plans. Then visit Garadain Galcierbane's camp say &quot;I have the Ry'Gorr Invasion Plans&quot; he will tell you to give them to his lookout which is also in the camp. As soon as you do the lookout will tell you to bring him the Items off of Scarbrow's corpse. At that point it starts a war and Scarbrow brings his troops to the camp to attack.<BR>
<BR>
Notes:<BR>
<BR>
Although the Avengers hit for up to 172 a time, with double attacks you should only need a single group with a couple of chanters, couple of tanks, a cleric and any class with an evac. Chanters AOE mez all the orcs, and the group then proceeds to kill Scarbrow loot and evac.<BR>
<BR>
Or one person can Kite the orcs, while the rest of the party kills Scarbrow, loot and then you can run the avengars into the Dwarves, who will have little trouble despatching them. Either is good.<BR>
<BR>
Sixth Segment: mithril Coldain Insignia ring<BR>
------------------------------------------------<BR>
<BR>
Give Korrigain your obsidian coldain insignia ring. He gives it right back. At this point, run away before Icefang agros. He will run, rather slowly, to the rygorr oracle camp near the dragon bridge.<BR>
<BR>
Outrun him, and with a full group of 50's, wait near the camp. When Icefang arrives, 3 oracles of rygorr and Poxbreath Yellowfang will spawn.<BR>
<BR>
Kill Yellowfang for his note. The note details that was responsible for the trickery. It was Rodrick the coldain.<BR>
<BR>
Now, go to the rygorr keep and sit near the one-way exit from crystal caverns. Eventually a Rygorr Emissary will spawn. Do NOT kill him, make sure he doesn't agro on anyone.<BR>
<BR>
A few minutes later, Rodrick will spawn next to him. Kill Rodrick, and loot his head.<BR>
<BR>
Give the head, the note and your obsidian insignia ring to Garadain. He will give you the mistral insignia ring.<BR>
<BR>
Notes:<BR>
<BR>
Roderick can be taken by a group of 35-40's quite easily, <BR>
<BR>
seventh segment: _________ Coldain Insignia ring<BR>
------------------------------------------------<BR>
<BR>
Now Garadain wants you to free the prisoner, Corbin.<BR>
<BR>
Go kill Warden Bruke. (They fixed him, he's much easier now, rare spawn instead of 4 MR guards that pop when you attack)<BR>
<BR>
Loot the shackle key.<BR>
<BR>
Give the shackle key and your mithril insignia ring to Corbin. He will make his &quot;escape&quot;.<BR>
<BR>
He walks to Dobbin Crossaxe's camp.<BR>
<BR>
Along the way 4 rygorr and 4 kromrif attack, including 1 named: Commander Bahreck.<BR>
<BR>
At all costs, get Corbin to his destination safely. Once he reaches that point, Dobbin will thank you and say something like<BR>
&quot;If you show me your insignia ring, I'll give you a note to give to Garadain&quot;.<BR>
<BR>
Notes:<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Eigth Segment: _________ Coldain Insignia ring (Endgame)<BR>
------------------------------------------------<BR>
<BR>
No information yet.<BR>

			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
			</tr>
